Microsoft plans to bring its personal assistant Cortana to numerous Internet of Things devices, including fridges and toasters. Cortana was created by Microsoft for Windows 10, Windows 10 Mobile, Windows Phone 8.1, and other platforms. Cortana is currently available in English, Portuguese, French, German, Italian, Spanish, Chinese, and Japanese language editions. According to ZDNet, Microsoft is bringing Cortana to IoT devices with its Windows 10 Creators Update – due out in March next year. The Cortana on Windows 10 IoT Core roll-out will begin with Cortana in English for the US and UK.